{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπιστέλλω</b>, <br /> <b>send to</b>, γράψας ἐς βυβλίον τάδε ἐπέστειλε ἐς Σάμον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.40; τοῖσι Ἕλλησι [prev. author] 7.239; ἡδίω.. ἂν εἶχον ὑμῖν.. ἐπιστέλλειν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.14; ἐ. ἐπιστολάς τινι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.37, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epistulae” 363b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>send a message</b>, τάδε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 770 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially by letter, <b>write word</b>, τοιαῦτα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 20.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περί τινος ὡς ἀδικοῦντος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.38; ἐ. ὅτι.. [prev. work] 50, 99 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἐπισταλέντα ἐκ τῆς Σάμου the <b>news received</b> from Samos,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 50; τὰ ὑπό τινος ἐπεσταλμένα 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Artoxerxes” 21. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. <b>enjoin, command</b>, τισί τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.37 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν ἄγγελον ἐπιστείλας ταῦτα ἔπεμψε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.4.32; τινὶ περί τινος [prev. work] 4.5.34 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: c.<i>infinitive</i>, ἐ. τινὶ ἀπίστασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.3; τινὶ ἐκμαθεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 863 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ Κῦρος αὐτῷ ἐπέστελλε πρὸς Πέρσας λέγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.5.26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ἐ. τινὰ ποιεῖν τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 106, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.5.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: without any case, <b>give orders</b> to do, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 205, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.72, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>give orders in writing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 24.13:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] — <i>passive</i>, ἔφη οὐδέν οἱ ἐπεστάλθαι ἄλλο ἢ ἀπαλλάσσεσθαι he <b>had received</b> <b>orders</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.131; καί μοι ἐκ βασιλέος ὧδε ἐπέσταλται [prev. author] 6.97 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἷς ἐπέσταλται τέλος to whom the office <b>has been committed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 908, compare “Eu.” 743; τἀπεσταλμένα [prev. author] “Ch.” 779; κατὰ τὰ ἐ. ὑπὸ Δημοσθένους 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀξιῶ ἐπισταλῆναί τισι c.<i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PRyl.” 121.13 (2nd c.AD): with personal construction, ταῦτα ἐπεσταλμένοι\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <b>having received</b> these <b>instructions</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.37 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in later writers, usually of <b>orders given in writing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.15.20, 21.25, “SIG” 837.14 (2nd c.AD)\">NT+2nd c.AD+</a>], etc.; of <b>orders</b> for payment, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1304 (2nd c.AD), etc. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1989","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιστέλλω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1909","matchingForm":"ἐπί","stepTransliteration":"epi","gloss":"upon/to/against","_zh_tw_Gloss":"在","_es_Gloss":"sobre/a/contra ","_zh_Gloss":"在"},{"strongNumber":"G1992","matchingForm":"ἐπιστολή","stepTransliteration":"epistolē","gloss":"epistle","_zh_tw_Gloss":"書信","_es_Glo